body:
This feedback was well-received a couple years ago, with 23 upvotes on Microsoft Connect, but hasn't been implemented yet. Basically, it would be really cool to be able to call a class constructor and "splat" the input parameters, and invoke static & instance methods the same way.

https://connect.microsoft.com/PowerShell/feedback/details/1376904/splatting-for-class-method-input-parameters

```powershell
class Person {
    [string] $FirstName;
    [string] $LastName;

    Person ([string] $First, [string] $Last) {
        $this.FirstName = $First;
        $this.LastName = $Last;
    }
}

$NewPerson = @{
    FirstName = 'Trevor';
    LastName = 'Sullivan';
    };
[Person]::new(@NewPerson);
```

